item.title: Janine add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "All morons hate it when you call them a moron. .." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "Goddam money. It always ends up making you blue as hell." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "It's funny. All you have to do is say something nobody understands and they'll do practically anything you want them to." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "This fall I think you're riding for—it's a special kind of fall, a horrible kind. The man falling isn't permitted to feel or hear himself hit bottom. He just keeps falling and falling. The whole arrangement's designed for men who, at some time or other in their lives, were looking for something their own environment couldn't supply them with. Or they thought their own environment couldn't supply them with. So they gave up looking. They gave it up before they ever really even got started." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by J. D. Salinger
item.description: "Don't ever tell anybody anything. If you do, you start missing everybody." -- J. D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by J. D. Salinger
item.description: "It's really too bad that so much crumby stuff is a lot of fun sometimes." -- J. D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I'm sick of just liking people. I wish to God I could meet somebody I could respect." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janine add a quote by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry
item.description: "Goodbye," said the fox. "And now here is my secret, a very simple secret: It is only with the heart that one can see rightly; what is essential is invisible to the eye." -- Antoine de Saint-Exupéry

item.title: Janine add a quote by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry
item.description: "People have forgotten this truth," the fox said. "But you mustn’t forget it. You become responsible forever for what you’ve tamed. You’re responsible for your rose." -- Antoine de Saint-Exupéry

item.title: Janine add a quote by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry
item.description: "Grown-ups never understand anything by themselves, and it is tiresome for children to be always and forever explaining things to them" -- Antoine de Saint-Exupéry
